The paper deals with supervised learning and regularization, which are core topics in machine learning. The use of various losses and their equivalence to rado losses make it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of regularization in boosting algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.ST (Statistics). Finally, the paper exemplifies the use of the ReLU loss in deep learning, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
